            and <ref href="/hk/cap542/s19">19</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><commencementNote>[1 January 1998]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403410763_002" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403410779_001" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Interpretation</heading><leadIn>In this Order—</leadIn><def name="ApprovedMap"><leadIn><term>approved
                    map</term>
                    (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">獲批准地圖</term>) means the map or
                maps—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438413199307_005" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>submitted together with the report referred to in <ref>section 18(1)</ref> of the Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap541">Cap. 541</ref>) by the Electoral Affairs Commission to the Chief Executive on 31 October 1997;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199307_013" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>specified in column 4 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199307_021" name="c" temporalId="s2_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>identified by reference to a plan number (Plan No.) prefixed “LCCA”;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199307_029" name="d" temporalId="s2_d"><num value="d">(d)</num><content>approved by the Chief Executive in Council on 11 November 1997; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199307_037" name="e" temporalId="s2_e"><num value="e">(e)</num><content>deposited in the office of the Electoral Registration Officer;</content></paragraph></def><def name="AreaCode"><term>area
                code</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">地區代號</term>), in relation to any
            constituency declared in this Order, means the code specified in column 3 of the
                <ref>Schedule</ref> and coloured red prefixed “LC” and followed by a number and
            described as “Recommended Legislative Council Constituency Area Code” in the legend of
            the relevant approved map;</def><def name="ConstituencyBoundary"><leadIn><term>constituency
                    boundary</term>
                    (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">選區分界</term>), in relation to any
                constituency declared in this Order, means—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438413199323_012" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>the boundary represented by the bold broken edging coloured red delineating, or partially delineating, that constituency and described as “Recommended Legislative Council Constituency Area Boundary which coincides with District Boundary and Urban/Regional Council Area Boundary” in the legend of the relevant approved map; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199323_020" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>the boundary represented by the broken edging coloured red delineating, or partially delineating, that constituency and described as “Recommended Legislative Council Constituency Area Boundary which coincides with District Boundary” in the legend of the relevant approved map, or that boundary and the “Recommended Legislative Council Constituency Area Boundary which coincides with District Boundary and Urban/Regional Council Area Boundary” referred to in paragraph (a), as the case may be; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413199339_006" name="c" temporalId="s2_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><leadIn>where any part of the boundaries specified in <ref>Schedule 2</ref> to the Interpretation and General Clauses Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap1">Cap. 1</ref>) joins or abuts any partially delineated constituency boundary mentioned in paragraph (a) or (b), as the case may be, or circumscribes or otherwise partially delineates that constituency—</leadIn><subparagraph id="ID_1438413199339_014" name="i" temporalId="s2_c_i"><num value="i">(i)</num><content>that part of those boundaries so specified; and</content></subparagraph><subparagraph id="ID_1438413199339_022" name="ii" temporalId="s2_c_ii"><num value="ii">(ii)</num><content>that partially delineated constituency boundary so mentioned.</content></subparagraph></paragraph></def></section><section id="ID_1438403410779_003" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Declaration of Legislative Council constituencies</heading><content>Each area named in column 2 of the <ref>Schedule</ref> and delineated on the approved map specified opposite thereto in column 4 of that <ref>Schedule</ref> is declared to be a constituency for the purpose of the first general election of persons to act as Members and the name of the constituency is specified opposite thereto in column 5 of that <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403410794_002" name="s4" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Number of Members to be returned for each constituency</heading><content>The number of Members to be returned for each constituency referred to in <ref>section 3</ref> is specified opposite to its name in column 6 of the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><schedule id="ID_1438403410810_001" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap542A/s2">ss. 2</ref>, <ref href="/hk/cap542A/s3">3</ref> &amp; <ref href="/hk/cap542A/s4">4</ref>]<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></note><content>
            
